<section id="images" class="scrollspy mt-2">
    <h3>Images</h3>

    <p>Add classes to an <code class="solo"><?=htmlentities('<img>');?></code> element to easily style images in any project.</p>

    <div class="docs-example docs-example-images">
        <img data-src="holder.js/140x140" class="img-rounded" alt="140x140" style="width: 140px; height: 140px;" src="data:image/png;base64,">
        <img data-src="holder.js/140x140" class="img-circle" alt="140x140" src="data:image/png;base64," style="width: 140px; height: 140px;">
        <img data-src="holder.js/140x140" class="img-polaroid" alt="140x140" src="data:image/png;base64," style="width: 140px; height: 140px;">
    </div>

    <pre class="line-numbers"><code class="language-html"><?=htmlentities('<img src="..." class="img-rounded">
<img src="..." class="img-circle">
<img src="..." class="img-polaroid">');?></code></pre>


    <h5>Image hover</h5>
    <div class="docs-example docs-example-images">
        <img data-src="holder.js/140x140" class="img-rounded img-hover" alt="140x140" style="width: 140px; height: 140px;" src="data:image/png;base64,">
    </div>
    <pre class="line-numbers"><code class="language-html"><?=htmlentities('<img src="..." class="img-hover">');?></code></pre>

    <h5>Image hover blur</h5>
    <p>The first effect that we’re going for is a simple blur. Long has man sought to blur pixels with CSS alone and now it’s finally possible with one little line of code!</p>
    <div class="docs-example docs-example-images">
        <figure><img src="/piment/assets/img/piment.jpg" class="img-rounded img-blur" alt="140x140" style="width: 140px; height: 140px;"></figure>
    </div>
    <pre class="line-numbers"><code class="language-html"><?=htmlentities('<figure class="img-blur"><img src="..." alt=""></figure>');?></code></pre>


    <h5>Image hover sepia</h5>
    <p>The second effect that we’re going for is a simple sepia <code class="solo">.img-sepia</code>.</p>
    <div class="docs-example docs-example-images">
        <a href="#" class="img-sepia"><img src="/piment/assets/img/naruto.jpg" class="img-rounded" alt="Naruto" style="width: 140px; height: 140px;"></a>
    </div>
    <pre class="line-numbers"><code class="language-html"><?=htmlentities('<a class="img-sepia"><img src="..." alt=""></a>');?></code></pre>

    <h5>Image hover grayscale</h5>
    <p>The third effect that we’re going for is a simple grayscale <code class="solo">.img-grayscale</code> .</p>
    <div class="docs-example docs-example-images">
        <a href="#" class="img-grayscale"><img src="/piment/assets/img/naruto.jpg" class="img-rounded" alt="Naruto" style="width: 140px; height: 140px;"></a>
    </div>
    <pre class="line-numbers"><code class="language-html"><?=htmlentities('<a class="img-grayscale"><img src="..." alt=""></a>');?></code></pre>


</section>